snippet.textDisplay: The best way to cook is to not measure anything and just wing it. I tried to learn how to cook following recipes and it sucked. Then I would just look at what we have in the pantry and fridge and imagine what goes good together and put it together somehow. I never measure anything. I can finally cook. I cook Thai food. When you don’t know where to start it’s definitely helpful to look at a few recipes, but figure out the quantity and whether or not you even want to add lemongrass, etc. and then do what you want. It’s liberating. And oddly enough, everything comes out pretty good for me.
snippet.textOriginal: The best way to cook is to not measure anything and just wing it. I tried to learn how to cook following recipes and it sucked. When you don’t know where to start it’s definitely helpful to look at a few recipes, but figure out the quantity and whether or not you even want to add lemongrass, etc. and then do what you want.
